    • Field Detail

      • protocol

        public String protocol
        Either "http" or "https". If null, pages for both protocols will be included.

      • hostname

        public String hostname
        A pattern representing the host name(s) to be selected from the crawl. This is allowed to contain at most one "*" character, which, if present, must be placed exactly before the first ".". The pattern must contain at least two specified inter-dot segments (e.g. "*.com" is not permitted as it would match too many entries).

      • pathPrefix

        public String pathPrefix
        A pattern which may contain "*" characters that is matched against the path part of the URL for the crawled items. Only crawled items for which the path starts as specified will be returned. If null, all items that match the hostname will be returned.

      • items

        public long items
        Number of items found so far (if complete is false) or in total (if complete is true).

      • complete

        public boolean complete
        Is the search complete?
